text.section:
The Well-being Committee may disclose information relative to an impaired licensee or certificate holder only when:
It is essential to disclose the information to further the intervention, treatment, or rehabilitation needs of the impaired individual, and only to those persons or organizations with a need to know;
Its release is authorized in writing by the impaired individual;
The committee is required to make a report to the board; or
The information is subject to court order.
